users.bio: I am focused on web development, data analysis, and data visualization. I have a broad range of professional experiences that gives me a unique perspective when solving and analyzing problems. I work well in a team and can adapt to new challenges. I was a soldier for seven years and an art teacher for three years. I have a bachelor’s degree in Art History and a Bachelor of Business Administration in Information Systems & Analytics from MTSU. I am currently attending Nashville Software School's Web Development Bootcamp. I am developing my programming skills and feel that I can learn new processes quickly. I find that success comes through relationships that encourage collaboration, communication, and results. I take great pride in serving as a trusted advisor to the customer’s technology needs.
